{We note that although} the HH band {has only a slight effect on} 
the formation of the TI state{, its inclusion is important when} considering the 
experimental detection of edge states.

{The importance of a} lucid theory {that accurately describes} spin 
properties of conduction electrons in silicon {with relatively simple
means is thus clear.}

{Although} technological issues resulting in threading dis-
locations and interface roughness {appear likely to affect the}
exciton linewidths{, the results of our calculations imply that}
reducing the compressive strain in the Ge quantum wells by
choosing a virtual substrate composition with a large Ge
fraction {will increase the} GAMMA-valley lifetime {because of the}
effects of intervalley phonon scattering.

{Good agreement was found between} the two approaches{, indicating that} 
the details of the quantum confined wavefunctions {are unimportant for} scattering 
{and that the} rates {are} primarily {determined by} the density of final states.
